article.headline: Southern Miss. 69, William Carey 44
article.story: HATTIESBURG, Miss. -- Jeremy Wise scored a game-high 17 points and Southern Mississippi defeated William Carey 69-44 on Monday night. The Golden Eagles (5-4) had four players in double figures, as Courtney Beasley and Craig Craft scored 12 apiece and Andre Stephens added 11. Southern Mississippi outrebounded the Crusaders 34-24 with Sai'Quon Stone, Stephens, Craft and Beasley notching six apiece. Marcus Spann and Dexter Middleton led William Carey with 16 and 13 points, respectively. The Crusaders were held to just 34.6 percent shooting from the field (18 of 52), including 5-for-13 from behind the 3-point arc.
